{"cursor":"5610","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n''). All the \"leaves\" in this image are bracts.]] In botany, a 'bract' is a\nmodified or specialized leaf, especially one associated with a reproductive\nstructure such as a flower, inflorescence axis, or cone scale. Bracts are often\n(but not always) different from foliage leaves. They may be smaller, larger, or\nof a different color, shape, or texture. Typically, they also look different\nfrom the parts of the flower, such as the petals and/or sepals.\n","linknr":193,"url":"Bract","recorded":1362482842,"links":45,"instances":["botany","botany","botany","botany"],"pdf":["http://www.textbooksonline.tn.nic.in/books/12/std12-botany-em.pdf"],"categories":["Plant morphology","Leaves"],"headings":["Variants","Bracteole","Involucral bracts","Epicalyx","Spathe","References"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/43/Yellow-rattle_close_700.jpg/220px-Yellow-rattle_close_700.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/91/Bougainvillea_glabra.JPG/120px-Bougainvillea_glabra.JPG","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3e/Banana_bract.jpg/90px-Banana_bract.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fd/E_milii_vulcanii_ies.jpg/120px-E_milii_vulcanii_ies.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d3/Ananas_bracteatus_var_tricolor.jpg/80px-Ananas_bracteatus_var_tricolor.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/0/00/Leafy-bract-Beggar-ticks.we.jpg/100px-Leafy-bract-Beggar-ticks.we.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e9/Hibiscus_rosa-sinensis3_ies.jpg/100px-Hibiscus_rosa-sinensis3_ies.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//u